----------------------------------------------------------
simReversi
 - a simple game engine for Reversi
   and released under BSD-style license.
----------------------------------------------------------

This is a simple game engine for the game Reversi.
The board is 8*8, and the coordinates for a move is (x,y), 
where x and y are from 1 to 8, used by commands.
The evaluton function of this engine is quit simple, 
which just count the number of black and white stones in the board.
Hope that optimization for that should be done by someone.
For Reversi, see: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reversi.

----------------------------------------------------------
Compile
----------------------------------------------------------
* For Linux Family
  make
* For Windows Family
  chose your perferred compiler.

----------------------------------------------------------
Run the game
----------------------------------------------------------
* Run simReversi
* Command q/p/d/s/n/u/w/b
  q     - Quite game
  p     - Print board
  d x   - set the search Depth x
  s     - Start game
  n     - return the Next move
  u     - move Undo
  b x y - move Black x y
  w x y - move White x y

----------------------------------------------------------

Have fun!

